<p>B. Enable cookies in your browser. <a href="http://www.whatarecookies.com/enable.asp">Here&#8217;s a link that explains how.</a></p>
<p><span style="color: #BE0000;"><strong> Why is it no longer opening in a new tab when I click on a Flower?  </strong></span></p>
<p>We had to change that because too many people were opening too many tabs and it was causing the Flowers to load really slowly. If you click on the sorry message you will get redirected to a new page where you can look for the next Flower to appear. Don&#8217;t stay on the same page and click the same Flower over and over (it&#8217;s not as fun that way). You can stay on a page and refresh, but I wouldn't recommend doing this it gets a little boring and this is meant to be a fun way to explore out site! </p>
